{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017CFoAwL6W15PcSZtFPCNQY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Version 2.0.0: Task-Oriented APIs Design\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-18\n     4→**Status:** Design\n     5→\n     6→## Problem\n     7→\n     8→Cloche's APIs (CLI, Web UI, gRPC) are oriented around workflow step runs. Users\n     9→interact with flat lists of runs identified by opaque IDs like\n    10→`develop-proud-nest-06cd`. In practice, the natural unit of work is the Task — a\n    11→ticket from the task tracker that may require multiple attempts, each involving\n    12→host and container workflows with multiple steps. The current model forces users\n    13→to mentally reconstruct the task/attempt hierarchy from flat run lists.\n    14→\n    15→## Solution\n    16→\n    17→Promote Task and Attempt to first-class domain concepts. Every workflow\n    18→execution belongs to a Task and an Attempt. The CLI, Web UI, and gRPC APIs\n    19→default to task-oriented views. Run IDs change to a colon-delimited format that\n    20→encodes the hierarchy: `attempt:workflow:step`. Existing data is automatically\n    21→migrated on first v2 startup.\n    22→\n    23→---\n    24→\n    25→## Design Details\n    26→\n    27→### Domain Model\n    28→\n    29→Three new/refined concepts:\n    30→\n    31→**Task** — The top-level work unit. Has an ID from the ticket tracker (e.g.\n    32→`cloche-123`). For manual `cloche run` invocations without a task ID, a\n    33→\"User-Initiated\" task is auto-generated with a unique ID.\n    34→\n    35→**Attempt** — One try at completing a task. Has a short generated ID (e.g.\n    36→`a12z`), start time, end time, and a tracked list of all workflow step\n    37→executions triggered. A new attempt is created each time the orchestration loop\n    38→picks up a task ID, or when a user manually runs a workflow against an existing\n    39→task.\n    40→\n    41→**Step Execution** — A single workflow step within an attempt. Identified by the\n    42→colon-delimited ID `attempt:workflow:step` (e.g. `a12z:develop:implement`). A\n    43→full workflow execution is addressed as `attempt:workflow` (e.g.\n    44→`a12z:develop`).\n    45→\n    46→```\n    47→Task (cloche-123)\n    48→├── Attempt (a12z)\n    49→│   ├── a12z:main:prepare-prompt\n    50→│   ├── a12z:develop:implement\n    51→│   ├── a12z:develop:test\n    52→│   └── a12z:main:finalize\n    53→└── Attempt (b34x)\n    54→    ├── b34x:main:prepare-prompt\n    55→    ├── b34x:develop:implement\n    56→    ├── b34x:develop:test\n    57→    └── b34x:main:finalize\n    58→```\n    59→\n    60→#### Domain types\n    61→\n    62→New types in `internal/domain/`:\n    63→\n    64→```go\n    65→type Task struct {\n    66→    ID        string\n    67→    Title     string\n    68→    Status    TaskStatus   // derived from latest attempt\n    69→    Attempts  []*Attempt\n    70→}\n    71→\n    72→type Attempt struct {\n    73→    ID        string\n    74→    TaskID    string\n    75→    StartedAt time.Time\n    76→    EndedAt   time.Time\n    77→    Result    string       // \"succeeded\", \"failed\", \"cancelled\", \"running\"\n    78→}\n    79→```\n    80→\n    81→The existing `Run` struct is replaced or significantly narrowed. Step executions\n    82→link to an attempt via `AttemptID` and are identified by the\n    83→`attempt:workflow:step` triple.\n    84→\n    85→Task status is derived from the **latest attempt only** — no more aggregating\n    86→across all runs for a task.\n    87→\n    88→### Database Schema\n    89→\n    90→New tables:\n    91→\n    92→```sql\n    93→CREATE TABLE tasks (\n    94→    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n    95→    title TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n    96→    source TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'external',  -- 'external' | 'user-initiated'\n    97→    project_dir TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n    98→    created_at DATETIME NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP\n    99→);\n   100→\n   101→CREATE TABLE attempts (\n   102→    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n   103→    task_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES tasks(id),\n   104→    started_at DATETIME NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,\n   105→    ended_at DATETIME,\n   106→    result TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'running',\n   107→    project_dir TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT ''\n   108→);\n   109→```\n   110→\n   111→The existing `runs` table is refactored to track step executions, with an\n   112→`attempt_id` column replacing the current standalone identity. Existing columns\n   113→that belong to the task or attempt level (`task_id`, `task_title`, etc.) move to\n   114→their respective tables.\n   115→\n   116→A join table links log files to attempts:\n   117→\n   118→```sql\n   119→CREATE TABLE attempt_logs (\n   120→    attempt_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES attempts(id),\n   121→    workflow TEXT NOT NULL,\n   122→    step_name TEXT NOT NULL,\n   123→    file_path TEXT NOT NULL,\n   124→    file_type TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'full',\n   125→    file_size INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n   126→    PRIMARY KEY (attempt_id, workflow, step_name, file_type)\n   127→);\n   128→```\n   129→\n   130→### ID Format\n   131→\n   132→**Attempt IDs** are short, URL-safe, human-typeable strings (4 alphanumeric\n   133→characters, e.g. `a12z`). Generated randomly with collision retry.\n   134→\n   135→**Step execution IDs** are colon-delimited: `attempt:workflow:step`.\n   136→- `a12z` — the attempt\n   137→- `a12z:develop` — a workflow execution within the attempt\n   138→- `a12z:develop:implement` — a specific step\n   139→\n   140→This format is used in CLI output, log paths, and API responses. The colon\n   141→delimiter is chosen because it is shell-safe (no quoting needed) and visually\n   142→distinct.\n   143→\n   144→### Log File Layout\n   145→\n   146→Logs move from the current per-run layout:\n   147→\n   148→```\n   149→.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step>.log\n   150→```\n   151→\n   152→To a task/attempt hierarchy:\n   153→\n   154→```\n   155→.cloche/logs/<task-id>/<attempt-id>/<workflow>-<step>.log\n   156→```\n   157→\n   158→Example: `.cloche/logs/cloche-123/a12z/develop-implement.log`\n   159→\n   160→Workflow-dispatch steps (e.g. `main:develop`) do not capture their own output\n   161→because the dispatched workflow has its own step logs. This avoids duplication —\n   162→`main-develop.log` does not exist; instead the output lives under\n   163→`develop-implement.log`, `develop-test.log`, etc.\n   164→\n   165→The `full.log` unified log file moves to\n   166→`.cloche/logs/<task-id>/<attempt-id>/full.log`.\n   167→\n   168→### CLI Changes\n   169→\n   170→#### `cloche list`\n   171→\n   172→Default view becomes task-oriented:\n   173→\n   174→```\n   175→TASK ID       STATUS     TITLE                           ATTEMPTS  LATEST\n   176→cloche-123    running    Fix the card renderer            2         b34x\n   177→cloche-456    succeeded  Add pagination to search         1         c78y\n   178→user-a1b2     failed     (user-initiated)                 1         d90z\n   179→```\n   180→\n   181→Flags:\n   182→- `--all` — all projects\n   183→- `--project <dir>` — specific project\n   184→- `--state <s>` — filter by task status (derived from latest attempt)\n   185→- `--limit <n>` — limit results\n   186→\n   187→#### `cloche status <id>`\n   188→\n   189→Accepts either a task ID or an attempt-prefixed ID:\n   190→\n   191→- `cloche status cloche-123` — shows task with all attempts, steps in latest\n   192→  attempt\n   193→- `cloche status a12z` — shows a specific attempt with its steps\n   194→- `cloche status a12z:develop` — shows steps within a specific workflow\n   195→  execution\n   196→- `cloche status a12z:develop:implement` — shows detail for one step\n   197→\n   198→#### `cloche logs <id>`\n   199→\n   200→- `cloche logs a12z:develop:implement` — logs for a specific step\n   201→- `cloche logs a12z:develop` — interleaved logs for all steps in a workflow\n   202→- `cloche logs a12z` — interleaved logs for the full attempt\n   203→\n   204→The existing `-f`, `-l`, `-s`, `--type` flags continue to work.\n   205→\n   206→#### `cloche run`\n   207→\n   208→- `cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"...\"` — creates a User-Initiated task\n   209→  and attempt\n   210→- `cloche run --workflow develop --issue cloche-123 --prompt \"...\"` — creates a\n   211→  new attempt under existing task\n   212→\n   213→### Web UI Changes\n   214→\n   215→The runs list page groups by task, with attempts nested under each task. Task\n   216→status is derived from the latest attempt.\n   217→\n   218→```\n   219→▼ cloche-123 — Fix the card renderer          [running]\n   220→    ▶ Attempt b34x (running)   2026-03-18 07:15\n   221→    ▶ Attempt a12z (failed)    2026-03-18 06:30\n   222→▼ cloche-456 — Add pagination to search       [succeeded]\n   223→    ▶ Attempt c78y (succeeded) 2026-03-18 05:00\n   224→```\n   225→\n   226→Expanding an attempt shows its workflow steps with the colon-delimited IDs. The\n   227→step detail view (accordion) serves per-step logs from the new file paths.\n   228→\n   229→The SSE streaming endpoint (`/api/runs/{id}/stream`) becomes\n   230→`/api/attempts/{id}/stream` and streams all step output for an attempt.\n   231→\n   232→### gRPC API Changes\n   233→\n   234→This is a v2.0.0 breaking change. Key RPC changes:\n   235→\n   236→- `RunWorkflow` response includes `task_id` and `attempt_id` (instead of just\n   237→  `run_id`)\n   238→- `ListRuns` becomes `ListTasks` — returns tasks with latest attempt info\n   239→- New `GetTask(task_id)` RPC — returns task with all attempts\n   240→- New `GetAttempt(attempt_id)` RPC — returns attempt with step executions\n   241→- `StreamLogs` accepts the colon-delimited ID format at any level\n   242→- `GetStatus` accepts task ID, attempt ID, or full step ID\n   243→\n   244→### Shell Auto-Completion\n   245→\n   246→`cloche init` sets up shell completion for zsh and bash. The completion scripts\n   247→are written to a standard location and the user's shell rc file is updated.\n   248→\n   249→#### Installation\n   250→\n   251→During `cloche init`:\n   252→1. Generate completion scripts using Go's `cobra` or custom completion logic\n   253→2. Write scripts to `~/.cloche/completions/` (user-local, no sudo needed)\n   254→3. Check if `.zshrc` / `.bashrc` already sources the completion script\n   255→4. If not, offer to append the source line\n   256→5. Skip on Windows\n   257→\n   258→#### What completes\n   259→\n   260→- **Subcommands**: `cloche <TAB>` → `run`, `list`, `status`, `logs`, `stop`,\n   261→  `init`, `loop`, ...\n   262→- **Task IDs**: `cloche status <TAB>` → queries daemon for recent task IDs\n   263→- **Attempt IDs**: `cloche status a<TAB>` → queries daemon for matching attempts\n   264→- **Colon-delimited drill-down**: `cloche logs a12z:<TAB>` → offers workflow\n   265→  names; `cloche logs a12z:develop:<TAB>` → offers step names\n   266→- **Workflow names**: `cloche run --workflow <TAB>` → reads `.cloche/*.cloche`\n   267→  files\n   268→- **Flags**: `cloche list --<TAB>` → `--all`, `--state`, `--limit`, etc.\n   269→\n   270→Completion queries the daemon via a lightweight gRPC call (new `Complete` RPC\n   271→that returns matching IDs given a prefix and context).\n   272→\n   273→### Automatic Migration (v1 → v2)\n   274→\n   275→On first v2 daemon startup, if the database contains v1-format runs:\n   276→\n   277→1. **Create tasks** — Group existing runs by `task_id`. Runs with empty\n   278→   `task_id` get a generated User-Initiated task.\n   279→2. **Create attempts** — Each run becomes an attempt. Multiple runs with the\n   280→   same `task_id` become separate attempts ordered by `started_at`.\n   281→3. **Migrate step data** — Step execution records link to their new attempt.\n   282→4. **Move log files** — For each migrated run, move files from\n   283→   `.cloche/<run-id>/output/` to `.cloche/logs/<task-id>/<attempt-id>/`. The old\n   284→   directory is removed after successful copy.\n   285→5. **Rename containers** — Docker containers named with old run IDs continue to\n   286→   work (they are addressed by container ID internally). No container rename\n   287→   needed.\n   288→\n   289→The migration is idempotent — a version marker in the database prevents\n   290→re-running.\n   291→\n   292→### Error Handling\n   293→\n   294→- If migration fails partway, the version marker is not set, so it retries on\n   295→  next startup. Individual run migrations that fail are logged and skipped.\n   296→- If the daemon cannot reach the task tracker, User-Initiated task IDs are\n   297→  generated locally (no external dependency for ID generation).\n   298→- Shell completion gracefully degrades — if the daemon is not running,\n   299→  subcommands and flags still complete (static); only dynamic completions (task\n   300→  IDs, attempt IDs) are skipped.\n   301→\n   302→## Alternatives Considered\n   303→\n   304→**Keep runs as the primary concept, just improve grouping** — Rejected because\n   305→the mismatch between what users care about (tasks) and what the system tracks\n   306→(runs) creates friction at every layer. Better to fix the model than paper over\n   307→it with UI grouping.\n   308→\n   309→**Use the existing run ID format with a task prefix** — e.g.\n   310→`cloche-123/develop-proud-nest-06cd`. Rejected because it doesn't solve the\n   311→attempt tracking problem and the IDs become unwieldy.\n   312→\n   313→**Store completion scripts in `/usr/local`** — Rejected in favor of\n   314→`~/.cloche/completions/` to avoid requiring sudo and to keep everything\n   315→user-local.\n   316→\n   317→## Resolved Questions\n   318→\n   319→- **`cloche list` verbosity**: Per-attempt detail lives in `cloche status\n   320→  <task-id>`. `cloche list` stays concise — one row per task.\n   321→- **Attempt ID generation**: Random 4-character alphanumeric (lowercase +\n   322→  digits). Uniqueness is scoped to the parent task, not global. On generation,\n   323→  retry if the ID collides with an existing attempt for the same task.\n   324→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ef967e69-c92c-4fc4-95b4-717af6719977","uuid":"302f50c6-a014-4bbe-a030-e7f53a7e315e","timestamp":"2026-03-18T19:07:40.766Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-18-task-oriented-apis-design.md","content":"# Version 2.0.0: Task-Oriented APIs Design\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-18\n**Status:** Design\n\n## Problem\n\nCloche's APIs (CLI, Web UI, gRPC) are oriented around workflow step runs. Users\ninteract with flat lists of runs identified by opaque IDs like\n`develop-proud-nest-06cd`. In practice, the natural unit of work is the Task — a\nticket from the task tracker that may require multiple attempts, each involving\nhost and container workflows with multiple steps. The current model forces users\nto mentally reconstruct the task/attempt hierarchy from flat run lists.\n\n## Solution\n\nPromote Task and Attempt to first-class domain concepts. Every workflow\nexecution belongs to a Task and an Attempt. The CLI, Web UI, and gRPC APIs\ndefault to task-oriented views. Run IDs change to a colon-delimited format that\nencodes the hierarchy: `attempt:workflow:step`. Existing data is automatically\nmigrated on first v2 startup.\n\n---\n\n## Design Details\n\n### Domain Model\n\nThree new/refined concepts:\n\n**Task** — The top-level work unit. Has an ID from the ticket tracker (e.g.\n`cloche-123`). For manual `cloche run` invocations without a task ID, a\n\"User-Initiated\" task is auto-generated with a unique ID.\n\n**Attempt** — One try at completing a task. Has a short generated ID (e.g.\n`a12z`), start time, end time, and a tracked list of all workflow step\nexecutions triggered. A new attempt is created each time the orchestration loop\npicks up a task ID, or when a user manually runs a workflow against an existing\ntask.\n\n**Step Execution** — A single workflow step within an attempt. Identified by the\ncolon-delimited ID `attempt:workflow:step` (e.g. `a12z:develop:implement`). A\nfull workflow execution is addressed as `attempt:workflow` (e.g.\n`a12z:develop`).\n\n```\nTask (cloche-123)\n├── Attempt (a12z)\n│   ├── a12z:main:prepare-prompt\n│   ├── a12z:develop:implement\n│   ├── a12z:develop:test\n│   └── a12z:main:finalize\n└── Attempt (b34x)\n    ├── b34x:main:prepare-prompt\n    ├── b34x:develop:implement\n    ├── b34x:develop:test\n    └── b34x:main:finalize\n```\n\n#### Domain types\n\nNew types in `internal/domain/`:\n\n```go\ntype Task struct {\n    ID        string\n    Title     string\n    Status    TaskStatus   // derived from latest attempt\n    Attempts  []*Attempt\n}\n\ntype Attempt struct {\n    ID        string\n    TaskID    string\n    StartedAt time.Time\n    EndedAt   time.Time\n    Result    string       // \"succeeded\", \"failed\", \"cancelled\", \"running\"\n}\n```\n\nThe existing `Run` struct is replaced or significantly narrowed. Step executions\nlink to an attempt via `AttemptID` and are identified by the\n`attempt:workflow:step` triple.\n\nTask status is derived from the **latest attempt only** — no more aggregating\nacross all runs for a task.\n\n### Database Schema\n\nNew tables:\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE tasks (\n    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n    title TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n    source TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'external',  -- 'external' | 'user-initiated'\n    project_dir TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n    created_at DATETIME NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE attempts (\n    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n    task_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES tasks(id),\n    started_at DATETIME NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,\n    ended_at DATETIME,\n    result TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'running',\n    project_dir TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT ''\n);\n```\n\nThe existing `runs` table is refactored to track step executions, with an\n`attempt_id` column replacing the current standalone identity. Existing columns\nthat belong to the task or attempt level (`task_id`, `task_title`, etc.) move to\ntheir respective tables.\n\nA join table links log files to attempts:\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE attempt_logs (\n    attempt_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES attempts(id),\n    workflow TEXT NOT NULL,\n    step_name TEXT NOT NULL,\n    file_path TEXT NOT NULL,\n    file_type TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'full',\n    file_size INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n    PRIMARY KEY (attempt_id, workflow, step_name, file_type)\n);\n```\n\n### ID Format\n\n**Attempt IDs** are short, URL-safe, human-typeable strings (4 alphanumeric\ncharacters, e.g. `a12z`). Generated randomly with collision retry.\n\n**Step execution IDs** are colon-delimited: `attempt:workflow:step`.\n- `a12z` — the attempt\n- `a12z:develop` — a workflow execution within the attempt\n- `a12z:develop:implement` — a specific step\n\nThis format is used in CLI output, log paths, and API responses. The colon\ndelimiter is chosen because it is shell-safe (no quoting needed) and visually\ndistinct.\n\n### Log File Layout\n\nLogs move from the current per-run layout:\n\n```\n.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step>.log\n```\n\nTo a task/attempt hierarchy:\n\n```\n.cloche/logs/<task-id>/<attempt-id>/<workflow>-<step>.log\n```\n\nExample: `.cloche/logs/cloche-123/a12z/develop-implement.log`\n\nWorkflow-dispatch steps (e.g. `main:develop`) do not capture their own output\nbecause the dispatched workflow has its own step logs. This avoids duplication —\n`main-develop.log` does not exist; instead the output lives under\n`develop-implement.log`, `develop-test.log`, etc.\n\nThe `full.log` unified log file moves to\n`.cloche/logs/<task-id>/<attempt-id>/full.log`.\n\n### CLI Changes\n\n#### `cloche list`\n\nDefault view becomes task-oriented:\n\n```\nTASK ID       STATUS     TITLE                           ATTEMPTS  LATEST\ncloche-123    running    Fix the card renderer            2         b34x\ncloche-456    succeeded  Add pagination to search         1         c78y\nuser-a1b2     failed     (user-initiated)                 1         d90z\n```\n\nFlags:\n- `--all` — all projects\n- `--project <dir>` — specific project\n- `--state <s>` — filter by task status (derived from latest attempt)\n- `--limit <n>` — limit results\n\n#### `cloche status <id>`\n\nAccepts either a task ID or an attempt-prefixed ID:\n\n- `cloche status cloche-123` — shows task with all attempts, steps in latest\n  attempt\n- `cloche status a12z` — shows a specific attempt with its steps\n- `cloche status a12z:develop` — shows steps within a specific workflow\n  execution\n- `cloche status a12z:develop:implement` — shows detail for one step\n\n#### `cloche logs <id>`\n\n- `cloche logs a12z:develop:implement` — logs for a specific step\n- `cloche logs a12z:develop` — interleaved logs for all steps in a workflow\n- `cloche logs a12z` — interleaved logs for the full attempt\n\nThe existing `-f`, `-l`, `-s`, `--type` flags continue to work.\n\n#### `cloche run`\n\n- `cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"...\"` — creates a User-Initiated task\n  and attempt\n- `cloche run --workflow develop --issue cloche-123 --prompt \"...\"` — creates a\n  new attempt under existing task\n\n### Web UI Changes\n\nThe runs list page groups by task, with attempts nested under each task. Task\nstatus is derived from the latest attempt.\n\n```\n▼ cloche-123 — Fix the card renderer          [running]\n    ▶ Attempt b34x (running)   2026-03-18 07:15\n    ▶ Attempt a12z (failed)    2026-03-18 06:30\n▼ cloche-456 — Add pagination to search       [succeeded]\n    ▶ Attempt c78y (succeeded) 2026-03-18 05:00\n```\n\nExpanding an attempt shows its workflow steps with the colon-delimited IDs. The\nstep detail view (accordion) serves per-step logs from the new file paths.\n\nThe SSE streaming endpoint (`/api/runs/{id}/stream`) becomes\n`/api/attempts/{id}/stream` and streams all step output for an attempt.\n\n### gRPC API Changes\n\nThis is a v2.0.0 breaking change. Key RPC changes:\n\n- `RunWorkflow` response includes `task_id` and `attempt_id` (instead of just\n  `run_id`)\n- `ListRuns` becomes `ListTasks` — returns tasks with latest attempt info\n- New `GetTask(task_id)` RPC — returns task with all attempts\n- New `GetAttempt(attempt_id)` RPC — returns attempt with step executions\n- `StreamLogs` accepts the colon-delimited ID format at any level\n- `GetStatus` accepts task ID, attempt ID, or full step ID\n\n### Shell Auto-Completion\n\n`cloche init` sets up shell completion for zsh and bash. The completion scripts\nare written to a standard location and the user's shell rc file is updated.\n\n#### Installation\n\nDuring `cloche init`:\n1. Generate completion scripts using Go's `cobra` or custom completion logic\n2. Write scripts to `~/.cloche/completions/` (user-local, no sudo needed)\n3. Check if `.zshrc` / `.bashrc` already sources the completion script\n4. If not, offer to append the source line\n5. Skip on Windows\n\n#### What completes\n\n- **Subcommands**: `cloche <TAB>` → `run`, `list`, `status`, `logs`, `stop`,\n  `init`, `loop`, ...\n- **Task IDs**: `cloche status <TAB>` → queries daemon for recent task IDs\n- **Attempt IDs**: `cloche status a<TAB>` → queries daemon for matching attempts\n- **Colon-delimited drill-down**: `cloche logs a12z:<TAB>` → offers workflow\n  names; `cloche logs a12z:develop:<TAB>` → offers step names\n- **Workflow names**: `cloche run --workflow <TAB>` → reads `.cloche/*.cloche`\n  files\n- **Flags**: `cloche list --<TAB>` → `--all`, `--state`, `--limit`, etc.\n\nCompletion queries the daemon via a lightweight gRPC call (new `Complete` RPC\nthat returns matching IDs given a prefix and context).\n\n### Automatic Migration (v1 → v2)\n\nOn first v2 daemon startup, if the database contains v1-format runs:\n\n1. **Create tasks** — Group existing runs by `task_id`. Runs with empty\n   `task_id` get a generated User-Initiated task.\n2. **Create attempts** — Each run becomes an attempt. Multiple runs with the\n   same `task_id` become separate attempts ordered by `started_at`.\n3. **Migrate step data** — Step execution records link to their new attempt.\n4. **Move log files** — For each migrated run, move files from\n   `.cloche/<run-id>/output/` to `.cloche/logs/<task-id>/<attempt-id>/`. The old\n   directory is removed after successful copy.\n5. **Rename containers** — Docker containers named with old run IDs continue to\n   work (they are addressed by container ID internally). No container rename\n   needed.\n\nThe migration is idempotent — a version marker in the database prevents\nre-running.\n\n### Error Handling\n\n- If migration fails partway, the version marker is not set, so it retries on\n  next startup. Individual run migrations that fail are logged and skipped.\n- If the daemon cannot reach the task tracker, User-Initiated task IDs are\n  generated locally (no external dependency for ID generation).\n- Shell completion gracefully degrades — if the daemon is not running,\n  subcommands and flags still complete (static); only dynamic completions (task\n  IDs, attempt IDs) are skipped.\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n**Keep runs as the primary concept, just improve grouping** — Rejected because\nthe mismatch between what users care about (tasks) and what the system tracks\n(runs) creates friction at every layer. Better to fix the model than paper over\nit with UI grouping.\n\n**Use the existing run ID format with a task prefix** — e.g.\n`cloche-123/develop-proud-nest-06cd`. Rejected because it doesn't solve the\nattempt tracking problem and the IDs become unwieldy.\n\n**Store completion scripts in `/usr/local`** — Rejected in favor of\n`~/.cloche/completions/` to avoid requiring sudo and to keep everything\nuser-local.\n\n## Resolved Questions\n\n- **`cloche list` verbosity**: Per-attempt detail lives in `cloche status\n  <task-id>`. `cloche list` stays concise — one row per task.\n- **Attempt ID generation**: Random 4-character alphanumeric (lowercase +\n  digits). Uniqueness is scoped to the parent task, not global. On generation,\n  retry if the ID collides with an existing attempt for the same task.\n","numLines":324,"startLine":1,"totalLines":324}}}
